# AI Job Hunter тАФ Project Rules

Local-first Electron desktop app. pnpm monorepo. React 19 + TypeScript strict.
ESLint `--max-warnings 0` in CI тАФ every warning is a build failure.

---

## Shell

**Always use Bash (never PowerShell). Prefix EVERY command with `rtk`:**
`rtk pnpm build` ┬╖ `rtk git status` ┬╖ `rtk rg foo` ┬╖ `rtk fd src` ┬╖ `rtk bat file.ts`
Meta: `rtk gain` (savings stats) ┬╖ `rtk discover` (missed opportunities).
Use `rtk rg` not `grep` ┬╖ `rtk fd` not `find` ┬╖ `rtk bat` not `cat` ┬╖ `rtk pnpm` not `npm`/`yarn`.
Never `find -exec`, never PowerShell syntax. Git Bash paths: `/c/Users/...`

---

## Non-negotiable тАФ never bypass these rules

ESLint enforces all of the below in CI. Inline suppression is banned (`noInlineConfig: true`).

### Zero errors before marking complete

- `rtk pnpm lint:strict` тАФ zero ESLint errors/warnings
- `rtk pnpm typecheck` тАФ zero TypeScript errors
- No `console.log` in production code
- No `@ts-ignore`, `@ts-expect-error`, or `// eslint-disable`

### Branch + PR workflow

Never push to `main`. `rtk git checkout -b feat/name` тЖТ commit тЖТ `rtk git push -u origin <branch>` тЖТ `rtk gh pr create` тЖТ CI passes тЖТ user approves.

Verify branch before starting:
```bash
rtk git fetch origin && rtk git branch -r | grep $(git branch --show-current)
# If gone: rtk git checkout main && rtk git pull origin main
```

